Gauteng cops have arrested three suspects allegedly linked to ATM bombings in Gauteng on Saturday morning, in Tembisa. Cops found dye-stained money, explosives, four firearms, and bullets. According to cops spokeswoman Brigadier Athlenda Mathe, cops were following up on a tip-off when they identified the first suspect. “The 44-year-old man was cornered, and his vehicle was searched. Dye-stained money was found in the boot of his vehicle,” she said. You must be SIGNED IN to read comments Two more suspects aged between the ages of 28 and 35 were both arrested at a house in the same area. They were also found with dye-stained money as well as an unlicensed gun and explosives.  The trio will appear in the Tembisa Magistrates Court on Monday facing charges of possession of dye-stained money, unlicensed firearms, bullets, and illegal explosives.